# Instructions to Run the Project

1. Open the Kaggle Notebook.

2. Attach the dataset:

   * Accident Detection from CCTV Footage
   * https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/ckay16/accident-detection-from-cctv-footage

3. Turn ON Internet in Kaggle settings (required for MobileNetV2).

4. Run all cells from top to bottom.

5. The notebook will:

   * Load the dataset
   * Preprocess images
   * Train the CNN model
   * Train the MobileNetV2 model
   * Evaluate both models
   * Generate accuracy/loss graphs
   * Generate confusion matrix
   * Generate classification report

6. Output files generated:

   * accuracy_curve.png
   * loss_curve.png
   * confusion_matrix.png

7. To test a new image:

   * Provide the image path in the prediction cell.
   * Run the cell.
   * The model will predict:

     * Accident
     * Non Accident

## Expected Result

CNN Accuracy: 62%

MobileNetV2 Accuracy: 74%

MobileNetV2 performed better and was selected as the final model.
